HEADWORD: Incivism
<hw>In*civ"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>civism</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>incivisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lack of civism; lack of patriotism or
love to one's country; unfriendliness to one's state or
government.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
